## 4. TRIAL DESCRIPTION

Ovarian cancer is the 8th leading cause of cancer-related death in women. Its prognosis is poor, with diagnosis often made at an advanced stage.

Patient management has evolved in recent years with more radical surgeries and the introduction of maintenance treatment following neoadjuvant chemotherapy.
